<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-343-046  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 343 046  OV: 07 342 838.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  July 1989 v8 n13 p150(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Peacock Plus EVGA. (Allstar Microsystems Corp.) (Hardware Review)(one of 15 high-performance VGA card evaluation in '16-bit VGAcards stretch the standard') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, Catherine D.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>The Peacock Plus EVGA card from Allstar Microsystems Corp is amidrange-priced graphics adapter that offers midrange performance.andO;This card offers 1,024-by-768 resolution for a list price of $645for the 512K version, $545 for a 256K version.andP;  It contains 512Kof 100-nanosecond VRAM and supports Microsoft Windows-386.andP;  ARAM-resident Zoom utility provides the ability to scroll, pan, orzoom with your graphics or CADD software.andP;  A font editor modifiesfonts and creates new ones.andP;  A utility disk includes drivers forLotus 1-2-3, GEM, Ventura Publisher, AutoCAD, and both the 80286and 80386 versions of Microsoft Windows.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Allstar Microsystems Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Allstar Microsystems Peacock Plus EVGA (Circuit board).andO;Topic:     Video BoardsSpecial-Purpose Boards-CardsBoards-CardsEvaluationComparison.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Fact file. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Peacock Plus EVGAandM;FACT FILE Peacock Plus EVGA Allstar Microsystems Corp., 13885 Alton Pkwy.,andO;Irvine, CA 92718; (714) 951-1884andM;List Price: With 256K RAM, $545; with 512K RAM, $645.andM;Requires: 286 or 386 AT-compatible computer, VGA monitor (multiscanningmonitor required for 800 by 600 display resolution).andM;In Short:  The Peacock Plus EVGA's price and performance place it in themidrange, but its inclusion of a Microsoft Windows/386 driver and its abilityto display 1,024 by 768 distinguish it.andM;A midrange-priced graphics adapter offering midrange performance, AllstarMicrosystems Corp.'s $645 Peacock Plus EVGA goes beyond the norm in offering1,024 by 768 resolution and some interesting utilities.andM;Engineered around Tseng Labs' VGA chip set, the 9-1/4-inch XT-height PeacockPlus board comes fully populated with 512K of 100-nanosecond VRAM.andP;  (You canbuy the board partially populated with 256K VRAM, the Peacock, for $545.)andO;</TEXT></DOC>